Edit - Charfoot:  Nope - AA crits and innate crits are 2 separate categories of crits.  You will never Innate crit more than 2% of the time, and never for more than an extra 55% damage.   You will never AA crit more than 20% of the time, and your damage will be double damage if you have reached SCF3 or higher.  The percentages listed above are total percentages at that stage, and are not additive, (although each crit AA level adds a set percentage to your total likelihood of critting) and depend on your progression through the crit AAs.  NB:  SCFM1 has SCF3 as a prerequisite.<br>
<br>
Example, if you have SCF3, SCFM2, and FOMM2, you will crit for double damage 15% of the time (SCF3=7%, SCFM2=4%, FOMM2=4%, and 7+4+4=15) , and 2% of the time you will innately crit for a random amount of damage between normal (100%) and 155% of normal damage.<br>
<br>
The 2,5,7,11,... progression listed above assumes a standard SCF1-3, SCFM1-3, FOMM1-3 progression (in that order) for simplicity's sake (and also because of the prerequisites for the crit AAs), and also to keep this a mini-FAQ for quick-reference, rather than a full-blown FAQ.<br>
